title: Photofission cross section of Uranium-234 in the energy region from 5 to 9 MeV and its comparison with the data for thorium-232 and Neptunium-237 in subbarrier region.

x4freetext: Photofission cross  section  of  Uranium-234  in  the
energy  region  from  5  to 9 MeV and its comparison
with the data for thorium-232 and  Neptunium-237  in
subbarrier region.

The Al-U-oxide target.  Thickness  of  U-234  -  0.63
mg/cm**2, U-238  - 1 mg/cm**2.  The U-234 target was
enriched in isotope U-234 to 92.8%  (U-235 - 6.7%,
U-238  -  0.5 %).  The  U-238  target  was  natural
uranium.
Stack of Th and U targets.
Mica-foils.
The unfolding  of the reaction cross section
using the iterational method from  the  experimental
reaction yield measured using the the direct fission
fragment counting.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Root-mean-square errors.
The measurements were performed by relative method  in
a bremsstrahlung  beam from microtron with  an energy
step of 25 keV  in subbarrier range (below 6 MeV)  in
the  frame  of one experiment with nuclei Th-232  and
Np-237.  The data for ratio  of  yields  of  (gamma,f)
reaction cross sections  are reconstructed from these
data  and presented  in  the  tables.  The  resonance
structures  of  photofission cross sections  of three
nuclei  are compared with each other.  The  resonance
structure  with  an average spacing  of about 0.1 MeV
is   confirmed.  The  angular   components   of   the
photofission    cross   section    for   U-234   were
calculated.  The energy dependence  of the quadrupole
component shows on the manifesting of fission channel
with quantum characteristics j-pi = 2+ and K = 1.
Data were prepared in  the MSU  INP  CDFE
by V.V.Varlamov.
